# Task-based user research

A detailed user research exercise that tests if users can accomplish the required task using the documentation.

Work with a user researcher if possible.

Use a discussion guide. Link to example.

Have a consent form.

Record the sessions if possible.

Have multiple users try to accomplish the task.

Be in the room and make notes.

Analyse and iterate.
